<div id="outline-container-org3079fe6" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org3079fe6">[CSS Box Model] - 02:00:39</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org3079fe6">
<p>
The CSS box model looks at all the html elements as boxes 
</p>

<div id="org90c8ef5" class="figure">
<p><img src="./images/th-625111471.jpeg" alt="th-625111471.jpeg" />
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org5085eb2" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org5085eb2">Set width and height</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org5085eb2">
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">#box </span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">height</span> : 70px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">widht</span>: 70px;
}
</pre>
</div>
<p>
Note that the total width/height is calcultaed as follows:
</p>

<p>
Total height = height + top/bottom padding + top/bottom border + top/bottom margin <br />
Total width = width + right/left padding + right/left border + right/left margin
</p>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-orgf868b1b" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgf868b1b">Setting Margin &amp; Padding</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgf868b1b">
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.box </span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin</span>: 3px; <span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">/*</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">set top, bottom, left &amp; right values</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;"> */</span>
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">padding</span>: 4px; 
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">height</span> : 70px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">widht</span>: 70px;
}
</pre>
</div>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.boxMain</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin</span>: 7px 0px 2px 11px; <span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">/*</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">top=7px ,right=0px, bottom=2px, left=7px</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;"> */</span>
}
<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.boxLast</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin</span>: 7px 3px; <span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">/*</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">top &amp; bottom =7px , left &amp; right =3px</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;"> */</span>
} 
</pre>
</div>

<p>
We can also set individual margin/padding like this:
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.box1 </span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin-top</span>: 70px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin-bottom</span>: 7px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin-left</span>:8px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin-right</span>:9px;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org0074e14" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org0074e14">Setting Border</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org0074e14">
<p>
We can set border as follows
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.bx </span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">border-width</span>: 2px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">border-style</span>: solid;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">border-color</span>: <span style="color: #ffffff; background-color: #ff0000;">red</span>;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgcb358c5" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgcb358c5">Border Radius</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgcb358c5">
<p>
We can set border radius  to create rounded borders 
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.div2</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">border-radius</span>: 7px;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org5f47d0a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org5f47d0a">Margin Collapse :</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org5f47d0a">
<p>
When two margins from difference elements overlap, the equivalent margin is the greate of the two.
This is called margin collapse.
</p>

<div id="org7a30746" class="figure">
<p><img src="./images/sibling_collapsing.png" alt="sibling_collapsing.png" />
</p>
</div>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">*</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin</span>: 0;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">padding</span>: 0;
}
<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.box1</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">background-color</span>: <span style="color: #ffffff; background-color: #ff0000;">red</span>;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin</span>: 30px;
}
<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.box2</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">background-color</span>: <span style="color: #000000; background-color: #00ffff;">aqua</span>;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin</span>: 20px; 

<span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">/*    </span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">box-sizing: border-box;</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;"> */</span>
}
</pre>
</div>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css">&lt;div class=<span style="color: #2d9574;">"box1"</span>&gt;
        Lorem ipsum dolor sit, amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Et tenetur cumque culpa blanditiis asperiores nisi assumenda perferendis. Officiis culpa omnis magnam quas itaque enim mollitia, vel doloremque animi nostrum, possimus sequi, minima necessitatibus temporibus?
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=<span style="color: #2d9574;">"box2"</span>&gt; 
        Lorem ipsum dolor sit, amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Et tenetur cumque culpa blanditiis asperiores nisi assumenda perferendis. Officiis culpa omnis magnam quas itaque enim mollitia, vel doloremque animi nostrum, possimus sequi, minima necessitatibus temporibus?
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgbbc8015" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgbbc8015">Box Sizing</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgbbc8015">
<p>
Determine what out of padding and border is included in elements width and height. <br />
Can be content-box border-box
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">*</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin</span>: 0;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">padding</span>: 0;
}
<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.box1</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">background-color</span>: <span style="color: #ffffff; background-color: #ff0000;">red</span>;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">margin</span>: 30px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">height</span>: 2320px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">width</span>: 233px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">border</span>: 2px solid <span style="color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;">black</span>;
}
<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.box2</span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">background-color</span>: <span style="color: #000000; background-color: #00ffff;">aqua</span>;
    <span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">/* </span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">margin: 20px;</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;"> */</span>
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">height</span>: 20px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">width</span>: 100%;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">padding</span>:6px;
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">border</span>: 5px solid <span style="color: #ffffff; background-color: #808080;">grey</span>;
<span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">/* </span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;">fit the child container in parent container</span><span style="color: #2aa1ae; background-color: #ecf3ec;"> */</span>
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">box-sizing</span>: border-box;
}
</pre>
</div>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-html">&lt;<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">div</span> <span style="color: #715ab1;">class</span>=<span style="color: #2d9574;">"box1"</span>&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit, amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Et tenetur cumque culpa blanditiis asperiores nisi assumenda perferendis. Officiis culpa omnis magnam quas itaque enim mollitia, vel doloremque animi nostrum, possimus sequi, minima necessitatibus temporibus?
    &lt;<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">div</span> <span style="color: #715ab1;">class</span>=<span style="color: #2d9574;">"box2"</span>&gt; 
    &lt;/<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">div</span>&gt;

&lt;/<span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">div</span>&gt;

</pre>
</div>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-css"><span style="color: #6c3163; font-weight: bold;">.div1 </span>{
    <span style="color: #3a81c3; font-weight: bold;">box-sizing</span>: border-box;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
